verbose_text: In two independent leukemia studies, expression of TIFAB was reduced upon treatment with the bromo-domain inhibitor JQ1 in acquired resistant MLL-AF9; KRas-G12D leukemia cells and following suppression of MLL-AF9 leukemic stem cells by the NF-kappaB-inducing kinase (NIK).
evidence: suppression of MLL-AF9 leukemic stem cells by the NF-kappaB-inducing kinase
